  "prompt": "IRMA ANAND cutoff?",
  "response": "The IRMA Anand cutoff refers to the minimum score or percentile that candidates need to achieve in entrance exams like the CAT or XAT to be considered for admission to the Institute of Rural Management Anand (IRMA). The cutoff can vary each year based on several factors, including the difficulty level of the exams, the number of applicants, and the availability of seats.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding the cutoff for a particular admission cycle, it is best to refer directly to IRMA's official website or contact their admissions office. They typically publish the cutoff scores along with other relevant admission criteria each year.",
